Christinehof Castle.label: Christinehof Castle
Christinehof Castle.description: Christinehof Castle is a castle in Tomelilla Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. It was built between 1737 and 1740 in the German Baroque style. Wikipedia

Dover Castle.label: Dover Castle
Dover Castle.description: Dover Castle is a medieval castle in the town of the same name in the English county of Kent. It was founded in the 12th century and has been described as the "Key to England" due to its defensive significance throughout history. Wikipedia

Mugdock Castle.label: Mugdock Castle
Mugdock Castle.description: Mugdock Castle was the stronghold of the Clan Graham from the middle of the 13th century. Its ruins are located in Mugdock Country Park, just west of the village of Mugdock in the parish of Strathblane. Wikipedia

Jordberga Castle.label: Jordberga Castle
Jordberga Castle.description: Jordberga Castle is a castle in Trelleborg Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. It is inhabited and owned by Otto von Arnold, former member of the Swedish Riksdag for the Christian Democrats. Wikipedia

Hjularöd Castle.label: Hjularöd Castle
Hjularöd Castle.description:
Hjularöd Castle is a castle in Eslöv Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden.
The castle was first mentioned in 1391, but the current castle was built in 1894-1897. It was built on command of the former owner, chamberlain Hans Gustaf Toll. Wikipedia

Häckeberga Castle.label: Häckeberga Castle
Häckeberga Castle.description:
Häckeberga Castle is a castle in Lund Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. It dates back to the 14th century.
It currently hosts a restaurant and hotel. Wikipedia

Kronovall Castle.label: Kronovall Castle
Kronovall Castle.description: Kronovall Castle is a castle in Tomelilla Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. Wikipedia

Hässelby Castle.label: Hässelby Castle
Hässelby Castle.description: Hässelby Castle is a castle, located in Hässelby gård in the west part of Stockholm Municipality. It is since 2010 owned by SIVAB and it's opened for weddings, parties and conferences. Wikipedia

Citadel of Damascus.label: Citadel of Damascus
Citadel of Damascus.description: The Citadel of Damascus is a large medieval fortified palace and citadel in Damascus, Syria. It is part of the Ancient City of Damascus, which was listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1979. Wikipedia

Skipness Castle.label: Skipness Castle
Skipness Castle.description: Skipness Castle stands on the east side of the Kintyre Peninsula in Scotland near the village of Skipness. Wikipedia

Vannaröd Castle.label: Vannaröd Castle
Vannaröd Castle.description: Vannaröd Castle is a castle in Hässleholm Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. Wikipedia

Newbury Castle.label: Newbury Castle
Newbury Castle.description: Newbury Castle is the name of an English adulterine castle built by John Marshal during The Anarchy. It is located west of the town of Newbury in the English county of Berkshire. Wikipedia

Laudegg Castle.label: Laudegg Castle
Laudegg Castle.description: Burg Laudegg is a restored castle ruin near Ladis, a village in Bezirk Landeck in the state of Tyrol, Austria. Wikipedia

Zétrud-Lumay Castle.label: Zétrud-Lumay Castle
Zétrud-Lumay Castle.description: Zétrud-Lumay Castle is a castle in Jodoigne, Walloon Brabant, Belgium located in Zétrud-Lumay. Wikipedia

Burg Kreuzenstein.label: Burg Kreuzenstein
Burg Kreuzenstein.description: Burg Kreuzenstein is a castle near Leobendorf in Lower Austria, Austria. It was constructed on the remains of an early medieval castle that had fallen into disrepair and was then demolished during the Thirty Years' War. Wikipedia

Burg Rheinstein.label: Rheinstein Castle
Burg Rheinstein.description: Rheinstein Castle is a castle near the town of Trechtingshausen in Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. Wikipedia

Shigisan Castle.label: Shigisan Castle
Shigisan Castle.description: Shigisan castle was a Japanese castle of the Sengoku period, controlled by the Kizawa and Matsunaga clans. Wikipedia

Takayama Castle.label: Takayama Castle
Takayama Castle.description: Takayama Castle is a castle located in the city of Takayama, Gifu Prefecture, Japan. The castle was built on a mountain nearly 687 m in height and had many typical castle features, including a stone base, earthen walls and a surrounding moat. Wikipedia

Ruine Pflindsberg.label: Ruine Pflindsberg
Ruine Pflindsberg.description:
Ruine Pflindsberg is a castle in Styria, Austria.
Around 1250 Philipp of Spanheim, the Archbishop-elect of Salzburg, occupied the Ausseerland and the Ennstal in Styria. Wikipedia

Kururi Castle.label: Kururi Castle
Kururi Castle.description: Kururi Castle is a Japanese castle located in Kimitsu, southern Chiba Prefecture, Japan. At the end of the Edo period, Kururi Castle was home to a branch of the Kuroda clan, daimyō of Kururi Domain. Wikipedia

Öster-Malma Castle.label: Öster-Malma Castle
Öster-Malma Castle.description: Öster-Malma Castle is a castle in Sweden. Wikipedia

Karsholm Castle.label: Karsholm Castle
Karsholm Castle.description: Karsholm Castle is a castle in Kristianstad Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. Wikipedia

Cartier Castle.label: Cartier Castle
Cartier Castle.description: Cartier Castle is a château in Marchienne-au-Pont, a part of Charleroi, in the province of Hainaut, Belgium. Wikipedia

Björnstorp Castle.label: Björnstorp Castle
Björnstorp Castle.description: Björnstorp Castle is a castle in Lund Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. It was built in 1752 and reshaped in 1860-1880, with its final appearance set in 1868, by architect Helgo Zettervall. Wikipedia

Trollenäs Castle.label: Trollenäs Castle
Trollenäs Castle.description: Trollenäs Castle is a castle in Eslöv Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. It is known since the 14th century, and has been in the ownership of only two families, Thott and Trolle. Wikipedia

Mariedal Castle.label: Mariedal Castle
Mariedal Castle.description: Mariedal Castle is a castle in Sweden. Written accounts and the weather vane indicate the castle was built in 1666. The splendid interior of the castle provides stucco ceiling and wainscoting. Wikipedia

Marsvinsholm Castle.label: Marsvinsholm Castle
Marsvinsholm Castle.description: Marsvinsholm Castle is situated in Ystad Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden, 12 kilometres from Ystad. Wikipedia

Diepenbeek Castle.label: Diepenbeek Castle
Diepenbeek Castle.description: Diepenbeek Castle is a castle in Diepenbeek near Hasselt in the province of Limburg, Belgium. The building consists of a 15th-century donjon with a 17th-century main block. Wikipedia

Château de Vaulogé.label: Château de Vaulogé
Château de Vaulogé.description:
The Château de Vaulogé is a château in Fercé-sur-Sarthe near Le Mans in the Sarthe department of France.
It was built in the 15th century by Jean III de Vaulogé, and a town grew up around it. Wikipedia

Château de Saumur.label: Château de Saumur
Château de Saumur.description: The Château de Saumur, originally built as a castle and later developed as a château, is located in the French town of Saumur, in the Maine-et-Loire département. Wikipedia

Burgruine Reifenstein.label: Reifenstein Castle
Burgruine Reifenstein.description: Reifenstein Castle is a castle in Freienfeld, near Sterzing, in South Tyrol. It is located near a dried marsh, in the valley of the Eisack. Wikipedia

Duivenvoorde Castle.label: Duivenvoorde Castle
Duivenvoorde Castle.description: Duivenvoorde Castle is a castle in the town of Voorschoten, South Holland, in the Netherlands. It was first mentioned in 1226, making it one of the oldest castles in South Holland. Wikipedia

Fast Castle.label: Fast Castle
Fast Castle.description: Fast Castle is the ruined remains of a coastal fortress in Berwickshire, south-east Scotland, in the Scottish Borders. Wikipedia

Dalaborg.label: Dalaborg
Dalaborg.description: Dalaborg is a ruined castle in Sweden. Wikipedia

Svenstorp Castle.label: Svenstorp Castle
Svenstorp Castle.description: Svenstorp Castle is a castle in Lund Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. It was built in 1596 by Beata Hvitfeldt, a powerful lady-in-waiting to the Danish King Christian IV. Her architect was Hans Steenwinkel. Wikipedia

Örenäs Castle.label: Örenäs Castle
Örenäs Castle.description: Örenäs Castle is a castle in Landskrona Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. A German Boroque style castle approximately 8 kilometres from the center of Landskrona. The building as it looks today was raised in 1914-1918. Wikipedia

Bungay Castle.label: Bungay Castle
Bungay Castle.description: Bungay Castle is in the town of Bungay, Suffolk by the River Waveney. Wikipedia

Burgruine Eppenstein.label: Burgruine Eppenstein
Burgruine Eppenstein.description: Burgruine Eppenstein is a castle in Styria, Austria. Wikipedia

Guédelon Castle.label: Guédelon Castle
Guédelon Castle.description: Guédelon Castle is a medieval construction project located in Treigny, France. The object of the project is to build a castle using only the techniques and materials used in the Middle Ages. Wikipedia

Solre-sur-Sambre Castle.label: Solre-sur-Sambre Castle
Solre-sur-Sambre Castle.description:
Solre-sur-Sambre Castle is a castle in Solre-sur-Sambre in the municipality of Erquelinnes, province of Hainaut, Belgium.
The castle was built around the turn of the 13th and 14th centuries and retains much of the medieval structure. Wikipedia

Braine Castle.label: Braine Castle
Braine Castle.description:
Braine Castle is a castle in Braine-le-Château, Walloon Brabant, Belgium.
In 649 the Abbess of Mons St. Waudru ceded her "land of Ittre", including Braine, to the Chapter of Mons. Wikipedia

Burgruine Fohnsdorf.label: Burgruine Fohnsdorf
Burgruine Fohnsdorf.description: Burgruine Fohnsdorf is a castle in Styria, Austria. Wikipedia

Gunterstein.label: Gunterstein
Gunterstein.description: Gunterstein is a castle in Breukelen, on the river Vecht, that was the former home of the rich Dutch widow Magdalena Poulle. Wikipedia

Doornenburg Castle.label: Doornenburg Castle
Doornenburg Castle.description:
Castle Doornenburg is a Dutch castle from the 13th century.
The castle is located in the eastern part of Gelderland, near the village of Doornenburg. It contains a front-castle and a main castle, which are connected through a small wooden bridge. Wikipedia

Gujō Hachiman Castle.label: Gujō Hachiman Castle
Gujō Hachiman Castle.description: Gujō Hachiman Castle is a yamashiro, or mountain castle, located on Hachiman Mountain in Gujō, Gifu Prefecture, Japan. Wikipedia

Burgruine Mödling.label: Burgruine Mödling
Burgruine Mödling.description: Burgruine Mödling is a ruined castle in Lower Austria. Wikipedia

Reichenstein Castle (Trechtingshausen).label: Reichenstein Castle
Reichenstein Castle (Trechtingshausen).description: Reichenstein Castle is a castle near the town of Trechtingshausen in Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. Wikipedia

Crathes Castle.label: Crathes Castle
Crathes Castle.description: Crathes Castle is a 16th-century castle near Banchory in the Aberdeenshire region of Scotland. This harled castle was built by the Burnetts of Leys and was held in that family for almost 400 years. Wikipedia

Dunseverick Castle.label: Dunseverick Castle
Dunseverick Castle.description: Dunseverick Castle is situated in County Antrim, Northern Ireland, near the small village of Dunseverick and the Giant's Causeway. Wikipedia

Bernstein Castle.label: Bernstein Castle
Bernstein Castle.description: Bernstein Castle is a historical building in Bernstein im Burgenland, Austria, first mentioned in the 13th century. Wikipedia

Fraeylemaborg.label: Fraeylemaborg
Fraeylemaborg.description: The Fraeylemaborg is a borg in the village of Slochteren in the Netherlands. At present the Fraeylemaborg is a historic house museum, which had 29,106 visitors in 2013. Wikipedia

Rullingen Castle.label: Rullingen Castle
Rullingen Castle.description: Rullingen Castle is a castle in Kuttekoven in the municipality of Borgloon, province of Limburg, Belgium. Its situation in the valley of the Herk is very scenic. Wikipedia

Svaneholm Castle.label: Svaneholm Castle
Svaneholm Castle.description: Svaneholm Castle, on the shore of Lake Svaneholmssjön in Skurup Municipality, Scania, southern Sweden was initially erected in the 1530s by the Danish knight and royal advisor Mourids Jepsen Sparre. Wikipedia

Hasegg Castle.label: Hasegg Castle
Hasegg Castle.description:
Hasegg Castle is a castle and mint located in Hall in Tirol, Tyrol, Austria.
Construction was completed soon after 1300, when Hall was rapidly becoming the center of Tyrolean commerce and salt mining. Wikipedia
Hasegg Castle.Address: Burg Hasegg 6, 6060 Hall in Tirol, Austria

Fortress of Miolans.label: Fortress of Miolans
Fortress of Miolans.description: The Fortress of Miolans is a former fortress prison located in a remote area of Savoy between Italy and France. Wikipedia

Trolleholm Castle.label: Trolleholm Castle
Trolleholm Castle.description: Trolleholm Castle is a castle in Svalöv Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. The estate comprises 110 houses and a total of 12300 acres. Wikipedia

Heimburg in Niederheimbach.label: Heimburg in Niederheimbach
Heimburg in Niederheimbach.description: The Heimburg is a castle in the village of Niederheimbach in Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. Wikipedia

Burg Clam.label: Burg Clam
Burg Clam.description: Burg Clam is a castle in Upper Austria, Austria. Wikipedia

Cortewalle Castle.label: Cortewalle Castle
Cortewalle Castle.description:
Cortewalle Castle is a moated castle in Beveren in East Flanders, Belgium.
The castle dates back to the 15th century, and is one of the oldest in the Waasland. It is built of white sandstone, in Flemish Renaissance style. Wikipedia

Burgruine Greifenfels.label: Burgruine Greifenfels
Burgruine Greifenfels.description: Burgruine Greifenfels is a castle in Carinthia, Austria. Wikipedia

Burg Gutenfels.label: Gutenfels Castle
Burg Gutenfels.description: Gutenfels Castle, also known as Caub Castle, is a castle 110m above the town of Kaub in Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. It was built in 1220. Wikipedia

Aberystwyth Castle.label: Aberystwyth Castle
Aberystwyth Castle.description: Aberystwyth Castle is an Edwardian fortress located in Aberystwyth, Ceredigion, Mid Wales that was built during the First Welsh War in the late 13th century. Wikipedia

Burgruine Gradenegg.label: Burgruine Gradenegg
Burgruine Gradenegg.description: Burgruine Gradenegg is a castle in Carinthia, Austria. Wikipedia

Burg Festenburg.label: Burg Festenburg
Burg Festenburg.description: Burg Festenburg is a castle in Styria, Austria. Wikipedia

Burgruine Senftenberg.label: Burgruine Senftenberg
Burgruine Senftenberg.description: Burgruine Senftenberg is a castle in Lower Austria, Austria. Wikipedia

Burgruine Rauhenstein (Baden).label: Burgruine Rauhenstein
Burgruine Rauhenstein (Baden).description: Burgruine Rauhenstein is a castle in Lower Austria, Austria. Wikipedia

Burgruine Gallenstein.label: Burgruine Gallenstein
Burgruine Gallenstein.description: Burgruine Gallenstein is a castle in Styria, Austria. The ruined Gallenstein Castle hosts many concerts and exhibitions as well as the annual Festival St. Gallen. Wikipedia

Alt Eberstein.label: Alt Eberstein
Alt Eberstein.description: The ruins of Alt-Eberstein are the remains of the former Schloss Eberstein, located on a hill near the town of Ebersteinburg and directly upstream of the modern city of Baden-Baden, in the state of Baden-Württemberg, Germany. Wikipedia

Beauvoorde Castle.label: Beauvoorde Castle
Beauvoorde Castle.description: Beauvoorde Castle is a castle in Beauvoorde in Wulveringem in the municipality of Veurne, West Flanders, Belgium. Wikipedia

Kulla Gunnarstorp Castle.label: Kulla Gunnarstorp Castle
Kulla Gunnarstorp Castle.description: Kulla Gunnarstorp Castle is a castle in Helsingborg Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. The old castle was built in the 16th century by Jørgen Ottesen Brahe. In the 19th century there was also built a new one by Baltzar von Platen. Wikipedia

Schloss Straßburg.label: Schloss Straßburg
Schloss Straßburg.description:
Schloss Straßburg is a castle in Straßburg, Carinthia, Austria.
Today the castle hosts changing museum exhibits, and houses several ethnographic collections. Wikipedia

Dolwyddelan Castle.label: Dolwyddelan Castle
Dolwyddelan Castle.description: Dolwyddelan Castle is a Welsh castle located near Dolwyddelan in Conwy County in North Wales. It is thought to have been built in the early 13th century by Llywelyn the Great, Prince of Gwynedd and North Wales. Wikipedia

Knaresborough Castle.label: Knaresborough Castle
Knaresborough Castle.description: Knaresborough Castle is a ruined fortress overlooking the River Nidd in the town of Knaresborough, North Yorkshire, England. Wikipedia

Djursholm Castle.label: Djursholm Castle
Djursholm Castle.description:
Djursholm Castle is a castle in Sweden.
Djursholm is located in Danderyd Municipality, within Stockholm urban area. The castle includes building components from the late Middle Ages. Wikipedia

Vrams Gunnarstorp Castle.label: Vrams Gunnarstorp Castle
Vrams Gunnarstorp Castle.description: Vrams Gunnarstorp Castle is a castle in Bjuv Municipality, Scania, in southern Sweden. It was built in the 17th century by Jørgen Vind. 1838 it came to the Tornérhjelm family. Wikipedia

Antoing Castle.label: Antoing Castle
Antoing Castle.description:
Antoing Castle is one of Belgium's most original and well-known castles, situated in Antoing in Hainaut.
It was first mentioned in the 12th century. Wikipedia

Burtnieki Castle.label: Burtnieki Castle
Burtnieki Castle.description: Burtnieki Castle is a castle in the historical region of Vidzeme, in northern Latvia. It was built on the south shore of Lake Burtnieks for the Livonian Order around 1284. Wikipedia

Rauna Castle.label: Rauna Castle
Rauna Castle.description: Rauna Castle ruins are located in the village of Rauna, in Cēsis District, Latvia. The castle was the principal residence of the Archbishopric of Riga in which at for certain period each year it was visited the Archbishop with his entourage. Wikipedia

Dvigrad.label: Dvigrad
Dvigrad.description: Dvigrad, Docastei in Istriot language, is an abandoned medieval town in central Istria, Croatia. It is located in the Draga valley. The history of the settlement is prehistoric; it remained inhabited until the 18th century. Wikipedia

Loevestein.label: Loevestein
Loevestein.description: Castle Loevestein is a medieval castle built by the knight Dirc Loef van Horne between 1357 and 1397. Wikipedia

Castle Brederode.label: Castle Brederode
Castle Brederode.description: Castle Brederode, also called the Ruïns of Brederode, is located near Santpoort-Zuid. The castle was founded in the second half of the 13th century by William I van Brederode. Wikipedia

Marksburg.label: Marksburg
Marksburg.description: The Marksburg is a fortress above the town of Braubach in Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. It is the only medieval castle of the Middle Rhine that has never been destroyed. It is one of the principal sites of the UNESCO World Heritage Rhine Gorge. Wikipedia

Burgruine Gmünd.label: Burgruine Gmünd
Burgruine Gmünd.description: Burgruine Gmünd is a castle in Carinthia, Austria. Wikipedia

Turaida Castle.label: Turaida Castle
Turaida Castle.description: Turaida Castle is a recently reconstructed medieval castle in Turaida, in the Vidzeme region of Latvia, on the opposite bank of the Gauja River from Sigulda. Wikipedia

Sausenburg Castle.label: Sausenburg Castle
Sausenburg Castle.description: Sausenburg Castle is a ruined German castle on the edge of the Black Forest, just north of the town of Kandern in Baden-Württemberg, between the villages of Sitzenkirch and Malsburg-Marzell. Wikipedia

Rosenburg.label: Rosenborg Castle
Rosenburg.description: Rosenborg Castle is a renaissance castle located in Copenhagen, Denmark. The castle was originally built as a country summerhouse in 1606 and is an example of Christian IV's many architectural projects. Wikipedia
